<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h1 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-circles-sectors-and-arcs">Circles,=
 Sectors And Arcs</h1>



<p id=3D"introduction"></p>



<p>Here we will learn about circles, arcs and sectors, including how to fin=
d the area and circumference of a circle and how to find the area and arc l=
ength of a sector.</p>



<p></p>



<p>There are also circles, arcs and sectors worksheets based on Edexcel, AQ=
A and OCR exam questions, along with further guidance on where to go next i=
f you=E2=80=99re still stuck.</p>
</div>
</div>



<p id=3D"What-are-circles-arcs-and-sectors"></p>



<div class=3D"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-=
layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-are-circles-arcs-and-sectors"=
>What are circles, arcs and sectors?</h2>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Circles</strong> are round plane figures whose boundaries consis=
t of points equidistant from a fixed point.</p>



<p></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding=3D"async" width=3D=
"215" height=3D"216" src=3D"https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploa=
ds/2022/06/Circles-Sectors-and-Arcs-image-1.png" alt=3D"Circles, Sectors an=
d Arcs image 1" class=3D"wp-image-134540"></figure>



<p></p>



<p><u>Sector of a circle</u></p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Sectors </strong>are sections of a circle that are created by tw=
o radii and an arc.</p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Major sector </strong>=E2=80=93 a major sector has a central ang=
le which is more than <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-di=
splay=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xm=
lns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>180</mn><mi=
 mathvariant=3D"normal">=C2=B0</mi><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">.</mi></mrow>=
<annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 180=C2=B0. </annotation></seman=
tics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span cl=
ass=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6944em;"></span><span=
 class=3D"mord">180=C2=B0.</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Minor sector </strong>=E2=80=93 a minor sector has a central ang=
le which is less than <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-di=
splay=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xm=
lns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>180</mn><mi=
 mathvariant=3D"normal">=C2=B0</mi><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">.</mi></mrow>=
<annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 180=C2=B0. </annotation></seman=
tics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span cl=
ass=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6944em;"></span><span=
 class=3D"mord">180=C2=B0.</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Step-by-step guide:</strong> <a href=3D"https://thirdspacelearni=
ng.com/gcse-maths/geometry-and-measure/sector-of-a-circle/">Sector of a cir=
cle</a></p>



<p></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority=3D"high" deco=
ding=3D"async" width=3D"305" height=3D"305" src=3D"https://thirdspacelearni=
ng.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Circles-Sectors-and-Arcs-image-2.png" alt=
=3D"Circles, Sectors and Arcs image 2" class=3D"wp-image-134541"></figure>



<p></p>



<p><u>Arc of a circle</u></p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Arcs</strong> are portions of the circumference of the circle.</=
p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Major arc</strong> =E2=80=93 a major arc is greater than half th=
e circumference.</p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Minor arc </strong>=E2=80=93 a minor arc is less than half the c=
ircumference.</p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Step-by-step guide:</strong> <a href=3D"https://thirdspacelearni=
ng.com/gcse-maths/geometry-and-measure/arc-of-a-circle/">Arc of a circle</a=
></p>



<p></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding=3D"async" width=3D=
