<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-common-misconceptions">Common misc=
onceptions</h3>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong><strong>Radius and diameters</strong></strong></li>
</ul>



<p>You will notice some formulas use the radius whilst others refer to the =
diameter. Make sure you know which one the question gives you, this allows =
you to find the other if required.&nbsp;</p>



<p></p>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong><strong>Not including the correct units</strong></strong></li>
</ul>



<p>Remember the value of the radius, the diameter, the arc length and the c=
ircumference are measures of length.<br><br>The value of the area of a sect=
or or segment are measures of area and therefore the units are squared.</p>



<p></p>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong><strong>Not giving answer in terms of </strong></strong><span c=
lass=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span class=
=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/19=
98/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext mathvariant=3D"bold">=CF=80</mtext>=
</mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> \textbf{=CF=80} </annota=
tion></semantics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"tr=
ue"><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0em;"></spa=
n><span class=3D"mord text"><span class=3D"mord textbf">=CF=80</span></span=
></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>



<p>Sometimes the question may ask you to give the answer =E2=80=98in terms =
of <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><sp=
an class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w=
3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=3D"bold">=CF=80</m=
i></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> \bf{\pi} </annotation>=
</semantics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><=
span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.4306em;"></spa=
n><span class=3D"mord"><span class=3D"mord"><span class=3D"mord mathnormal"=
 style=3D"margin-right: 0.0359em;">=CF=80</span></span></span></span></span=
></span></span>=E2=80=99. This means you do not give the numerical answer t=
hat is produced when you multiply it by <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rende=
red" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"kate=
x-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mr=
ow><mi mathvariant=3D"bold">=CF=80</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"appli=
cation/x-tex"> \bf{\pi} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=
=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"st=
rut" style=3D"height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class=3D"mord"><span class=3D=
"mord"><span class=3D"mord mathnormal" style=3D"margin-right: 0.0359em;">=
=CF=80</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.&nbsp;</p>



<p></p>



<p>For example,</p>



<p></p>



<p><span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><sp=
an class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w=
